108
00:02:35,500 --> 00:02:37,800
Master Moria...

109
00:02:44,510 --> 00:02:47,020
He's... alive...

110
00:02:48,310 --> 00:02:53,020
“Gecko Moria and His Zombie Army Attack”...

111
00:02:54,020 --> 00:02:55,980
He's alive!

112
00:02:56,030 --> 00:02:59,740
Master Moria is really alive!

113
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:05,490
Look! It's amazing! Master Moria is alive!

114
00:03:07,450 --> 00:03:09,460
Yes, I read it this morning.

115
00:03:09,910 --> 00:03:14,500
And you didn't think to tell me, you jerk?!
This is very important to me!

116
00:03:14,500 --> 00:03:15,460
I don't care.

117
00:03:15,460 --> 00:03:18,340
You should! He's my captain!

118
00:03:18,880 --> 00:03:22,760
I thought he died in
the Summit War two years ago!

119
00:03:22,760 --> 00:03:24,430
I'm so relieved!

120
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:31,770
If Master Moria is alive,
maybe Absalom and Hogback are with him!

121
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:36,020
I just have to see him now!
Let's get a move on!

122
00:03:44,280 --> 00:03:46,030
Oh, yeah...

123
00:03:46,780 --> 00:03:49,910
He let me stay here for ages.

124
00:03:53,250 --> 00:03:56,670
Ever since Bartholomew Kuma
interrupted my confrontation with

125
00:03:56,670 --> 00:03:59,590
the Straw Hats at Thriller Bark
and sent me flying here.

126
00:04:00,050 --> 00:04:02,130
So it's already been two years...

127
00:04:03,340 --> 00:04:08,350
Moria is as tenacious as
the zombies he commands.

128
00:04:08,760 --> 00:04:11,310
Huh? Are you making fun of Master Moria?!

129
00:04:11,310 --> 00:04:12,890
You ungrateful jerk!

130
00:04:14,060 --> 00:04:15,270
I owe him nothing.

131
00:04:15,270 --> 00:04:17,060
You owe me!

132
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:20,320
Do you know how many times
I cooked for you?!

133
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:23,400
I cooked more than you did.

134
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:25,860
I helped with the farming, too!

135
00:04:26,320 --> 00:04:28,160
I let you stay here.

136
00:04:30,080 --> 00:04:32,080
You're so annoying!

137
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:33,080
Fine!

138
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:42,630
I'm leaving!

139
00:04:43,340 --> 00:04:44,300
As you wish.

140
00:04:46,180 --> 00:04:48,720
I'm glad nothing's keeping me tied here.

141
00:04:51,100 --> 00:04:52,930
Take care of yourself.

142
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:06,610
Now you're nice?!

143
00:05:06,610 --> 00:05:10,780
Damn you! Don't spring
those kind words on me!

144
00:05:19,250 --> 00:05:22,210
Thank you for everything!

145
00:05:24,380 --> 00:05:26,340
Such a noisome woman.

146
00:05:26,930 --> 00:05:27,630
But...

147
00:05:29,300 --> 00:05:33,310
the timing of your departure
is likely fortuitous.

148
00:05:33,310 --> 00:05:34,350
What?

149
00:05:37,810 --> 00:05:40,860
The Reverie at Mary Geoise
is currently underway...

150
00:05:42,610 --> 00:05:44,990
during which an odd topic has arisen.

151
00:05:51,740 --> 00:05:56,910
The New World
Pirate Island
Beehive

152
00:06:10,840 --> 00:06:12,720
Charge!

153
00:06:35,830 --> 00:06:38,750
Where's Absalom?!

154
00:06:38,750 --> 00:06:42,080
Where are you hiding him?!

